    section.white-tier.text-center.white-tier-press.no-bottom-border
        .container.featured-press
            .row
                .col-xs-12
                    h3.white-tier-title Featured press

            .row.row-flex
                .col-flex.col-flex-15
                    img(src="/images/featured_press_fc.png", class="img-responsive", alt="SmartUp Listed InThe 25 Best Free iPhone Apps For Business")
                .col-flex.col-flex-60
                    .featured-press-text
                        h5 SmartUp Listed In The 25 Best Free iPhone Apps For Business
                        p
                            | Hammer business fundamentals with SmartUp. The app features new 
                            | content every day, consisting of quizzes, games, case studies, and more 
                            | that cover entrepreneurship and innovation. 
                .col-flex.col-flex-25
                    a(href="https://www.fastcompany.com/3055902/app-economy/the-25-best-free-iphone-apps-for-business", class="cbtn btn-dark") Read more
            .row.row-flex
                .col-flex.col-flex-15
                    img(src="/images/featured_press_tc.png", class="img-responsive", alt="SmartUp has plans to shake up the changing MBA market")
                .col-flex.col-flex-60
                    .featured-press-text
                        h5 SmartUp App Virtually Mentors New Entrepreneurs And Could Lead To Funding
                        p
                            | But there is a twist. The app builds up a proﬁle of the user by asking the 
                            | same questions investors and mentors would if they were advising them in 
                            | person. The aim is to deliver insights and advice to help the users make 
                            | better decisions. 
                .col-flex.col-flex-25
                    a(href="https://techcrunch.com/2015/06/29/smartup-app-virtually-mentors-new-entrepreneurs-and-could-lead-to-funding/", class="cbtn btn-dark") Read more
            .row.row-flex
                .col-flex.col-flex-15
                    img(src="/images/featured_press_ft.png", class="img-responsive", alt="Edtech providers move from Moocs to social networking")
                .col-flex.col-flex-60
                    .featured-press-text
                        h5 SmartUp has plans to shake up the changing MBA market
                        p
                            | According to Frank Meehan, chief executive of SmartUp. “We don’t just 
                            | want the elite to be able to access business education,” he says. “We think 
                            | it should be open to the 24-year-old in Bangalore looking to start a 
                            | company himself who is nowhere near a business school but has a 
                            | smartphone.” 
                .col-flex.col-flex-25
                    a(href="https://www.ft.com/content/f6986c76-52c8-11e4-a236-00144feab7de", class="cbtn btn-dark") Read more
            .row.row-flex
                .col-flex.col-flex-15
                    img(src="/images/featured_press_ft.png", class="img-responsive", alt="Edtech providers move from Moocs to social networking")
                .col-flex.col-flex-60
                    .featured-press-text
                        h5 Edtech providers move from Moocs to social networking
